<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Resource_item_arm
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm">
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_group_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_group_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_group_relationship">
A <b>Resource_group_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship"/>

  that specifiies   the means to associate two resource items that are part of a resource group. The meaning of
the entity is determined by classification.

<example number="1">The relationship between a tool set and a mallet could be classified as "Contains".
</example>

<example number="2">The relationship between a facility and compressed air could be classified as "Provides".
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_group_relationship  Attribute: quantity 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_group_relationship.quantity"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_group_relationship.quantity">
the measure of the amount of related <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item"/>. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item">
A <b>Resource_item</b> is an item  that can occur in the role of a resource within the application context.
<example>
A resource item may be classified as "Facility", "Replaceble unit", or "Package".
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.name">
the text by which the <b>Resource_item</b> is known.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.description">
the text that further characterizes the resource item. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  Attribute: resource_item 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item">
the item that is designated as a resource within the application context.
The value of this attribute need not be specified.
<note>a resource may be an item or a type of item</note>
<example>
A <b>Resource_item</b> can be a product, product category, product version, serialized product, or person.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment">
A <b>Resource_item_assignment</b> is an association of   a resource item with some product information. The role of the assignment is determined by classification.
<example>
The assignment can be classified as "applicable to" or "acquired for".
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_assignment  Attribute: assigned_resource 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment.assigned_resource"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment.assigned_resource">
the resource item that is to be associated with an item.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_assignment  Attribute: item 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment.item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment.item">
the resource assignment item to which the resource item is assigned.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship">
A <b>Resource_item_relationship</b> is a specification of how a resource item may  be associated with another  resource item. The role of the relationship is determined by classification.
<example>
The relationship between a product and a package can be classified as "Preferred".
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.name">
the word or words by which the <b>Resource_item_relationship</b> is known.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.description">
the text that further characterizes the resource item relationship. The value of the attribute need not be specified.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  Attribute: relating 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.relating"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.relating">
one of the instances of <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item"/>

 that is a part of   the relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_relationship  Attribute: related 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.related"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_relationship.related">the other  instance of <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item"/>

 that is a part of   the relationship.  If one element of  the relationship is dependent upon the other, this attribute shall be the dependent one.

 </ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
